      <guid>https://www.adamormsby.com/projects/personal-blog/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;about&#34;&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I built this little blog on my own using the &lt;a href=&#34;https://gohugo.io/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; &gt;Hugo static site generator&lt;/a&gt;, and I&amp;rsquo;m super proud of it. It&amp;rsquo;s honestly the most fun I&amp;rsquo;ve had in developing a website in &lt;em&gt;years!&lt;/em&gt; I&amp;rsquo;ve learned a ton of things in the process, and I&amp;rsquo;m very capable of building websites using this framework. In fact, if you want a website for yourself or need one for your company, I&amp;rsquo;d &lt;em&gt;love&lt;/em&gt; to build it for you. Just get in touch with me through the contact links on my &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.adamormsby.com/about&#34; &gt;About page&lt;/a&gt; and let me know!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sometimes I write more technical posts about the work that went into building this site, and I&amp;rsquo;d love it if you check them out. The links below will take you to some of them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;links&#34;&gt;Links&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;posts-about-my-blog-setup&#34;&gt;Posts About My Blog Setup&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.adamormsby.com/posts/how-to-set-up-a-hugo-site-on-github-pages-with-submodules/&#34; &gt;How to Set Up a Hugo Site on Github Pages - with Git Submodules!&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;custom-work--add-ons&#34;&gt;Custom Work / Add-Ons&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&#34;projects-pageprojects&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.adamormsby.com/projects&#34; &gt;Projects Page&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My Projects page is a custom page layout that I built to be used within this site theme. I created a new site section called &amp;lsquo;projects&amp;rsquo; so the layout can read from all subdirectories and display each set of projects in a list. Each project is its own bundled page directory with all relevant media.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;content/&lt;br&gt;
__ projects/&lt;br&gt;
___| project1/&lt;br&gt;
___|___| img/&lt;br&gt;
