      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;about&#34;&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Back when I began traveling internationally, I decided to write my experiences in a travel blog. My posts included tips, travel information, and stories of personal connection with myself and the people I met along the way. I enjoyed writing my stories in particular, but I soon realized that most other aspects of travel writing - guides, histories, and constant photography - didn&amp;rsquo;t really appeal to me in the long run, so I decided to end the project and focus more on being present in my experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the sake of archiving a few things (and because I&amp;rsquo;m particularly fond of them), I&amp;rsquo;ve added my favorite set of stories here on this site. If cycling abroad is your thing, maybe you&amp;rsquo;ll enjoy reading them.&lt;/p&gt;
