    <item>
      <title>Luminus</title>
      <link>https://www.adamormsby.com/projects/luminus/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2014 00:00:00 -0500</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.adamormsby.com/projects/luminus/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;about&#34;&gt;About&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The company Faceshift asked me to create a tech demo for their new facial recognition software that would be on display at a tech conference. I had just over one week to put together a small team, design and create a game based on recognizing player facial expressions, and submit the finished product before the conference began. It was a tight schedule, but we did it!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The resulting game &lt;em&gt;Luminus&lt;/em&gt; was about capturing fireflies using only a set of simple facial expressions. Each different color of firefly the player encountered was connected to a different expression, and even the game menus could be used in the same way! This is one of the more unique projects I&amp;rsquo;ve worked on, and it was a great challenge to put together.&lt;/p&gt;
